parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt can cause the occupant to be unrestrained during an accident, leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle fails to latch
the seat belt does not retract properly
the seat belt fails to hold the occupant securely during an accident
the seat belt causes injuries or fatalities due to its failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt can cause the occupant to be ejected from the vehicle during an accident, leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The motorized seat belt releases unexpectedly
the motorized seat belt fails to restrain the occupant during an accident
the motorized seat belt causes ejection from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadvertent unlatching of the seat belt can cause the occupant to be unrestrained during an accident, leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the seat belt wraps around the seat position lever/dislodges while the car is in motion
the seat belt causes loss of control and accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Acceleration and Unintended Throttle Opening
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration and unintended throttle opening can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, as well as increased fuel consumption.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without driver input
the throttle sticks or becomes stuck
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly when shifting into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the throttle body assembly can cause sudden acceleration, unintended throttle opening, and fuel leaks, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fires.
symptoms: the throttle body assembly sprays gas onto the computer
the throttle assembly needs to be replaced due to fuel leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition distributor can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to potential accidents or strandings.
The failure of the relay can cause the vehicle to fail to start, particularly in high-temperature conditions, leading to potential accidents or strandings.
The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leading to potential accidents or strandings.
The failure of the igniter can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to potential accidents or strandings.
The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to potential accidents or strandings.
The failure of the fuel throttle body assembly can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to potential accidents or strandings.
symptoms: Fuel throttle body assembly sprays gas on the computer
